---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Install & Overview - Svelte">
  <div class="mb-4 text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
    @elekcsv/svelte
  </div>

  <h1 class="mb-8 border-b-2 border-black pb-4">3.1 Install & Overview</h1>

  <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    The <code>@elekcsv/svelte</code> package brings the same parsing pipeline from
    <code>@elekcsv/core</code> into Svelte with a store-first API. You keep full
    control over your UI while the importer handles parse, mapping, and validation
    state.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    You only need the Svelte package plus the core engine. The API works in
    Svelte 3+ and can be used in regular Svelte apps or SvelteKit.
  </p>

  <pre><code>npm install @elekcsv/svelte @elekcsv/core
# or
yarn add @elekcsv/svelte @elekcsv/core
# or
pnpm add @elekcsv/svelte @elekcsv/core</code></pre>

  <h2>Why Svelte Store API?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Reactive by default:</strong> Import progress and
      step transitions are exposed via a Svelte store, so your UI updates without
      extra state wiring.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Headless architecture:</strong> You render the dropzone,
      mapper, and review screens exactly how your product needs.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Same core performance:</strong> The importer uses
      <code>@elekcsv/core</code> under the hood for fast parsing and validation.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-16 flex justify-end">
    <a
      href="/docs/svelte/basic"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-black text-white rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-neutral-800 no-underline! transition-colors"
      style="text-decoration:none;"
    >
      Next: Basic Usage
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        ><path
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          stroke-width="2"
          d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"></path>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
